node.text:
making Billie Eilish’s Met Gala dress (in 2 days!)

In total, dress cost about $100 ($65 of tulle, $30 of spray paint), had 14 layers in the skirt, and was made in about 48 hours. The only reason I was able to make it so fast is because when you break it down, it’s actually a pretty simple style - it’s just a circle skirt with a cupped bodice! And then it’s just a matter of adding back the things that make it ✨fancy✨, the ombre, the layers, etc!

Again, this whole project was made possible thanks to Snapchat - they partnered with me for NYFW and challenged me to make a Met Gala look! Definitely check out my snap (my @ is shayshay2332, but if you search “Crescent Shay” I should come up as a verified creator!)

But that’s a wrap on this project - onto the next one!

Original gown designed by: @oscardelarenta 
Original gown worn by: @billieeilish 
Original gown stylled by: @denagia 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Recreating Billie Eilish’s Met Gala dress - a 2-day adventure. featuring one all nighter, 100 yards of tulle, and 5 cans of spray paint 😅

But y’all WOW - this project was a JOURNEY. And honesty, despite the chaotic timeline, it went really smoothly? And who knew - spray painting tulle works fairly well! And while there are definitely something I would change, there’s a lot I’m proud of in this gown. :)

This was a little bit ambitious and definitely forced me to work fast - but I think it was a really cool challenge to recreate something quickly like this! I’m having a lot of fun with these smaller 2 day builds,  so I think I may start sprinkling them in more often! 

And again - a HUGE thank you to Snapchat for partnering with me on these two project for NYFW! But now I’m back to sleep because I am still tired after pulling that all nighter (I think I earned a couple rest days after these projects haha)

node.text:
this weekend’s project: a recreation of a @moschino look from new york week fashion week, 2021! 

so my goal for it was to not stress about it being perfect, and just have fun with it and try to put it together in a day or so! and honestly - Iam surprised with how incredible this turned out despite the fact I was just kinda winging it?!! 

there were quite a few moments where I didn’t think it would come out good (not gonna lie, the plaid colors and painting in stripes had me nervous 😅) but it actually came out really really pretty 😭💕 and it’s a totally different style than the sort of thing I typically make!

(seriously though, I gotta make matching sets like this more often - I was very much feeling my legally blonde/polly pocket fantasy taking pictures in it, it was so fun!!! 😭💕✨)

bur this is actually the first of 2 projects I’m making for Snapchat for new york fashion week - so if you’d like to see a progress video, check out my snap! The next one is gonna be a recreation of one of this year’s Met Gala looks, and yall i am SO excited to make it!!! I’ll post a couple polls on my story in a bit, so we can vote on which met gala look i should make!
.
.

node.text:
making a fiber optics dress part 2: the top & the finished dress!!!!! 

y’all already saw the photos from our shoot on my page but I really think this is one of the dresses that needs to be seen on video/in person - once its moving the whole dress just comes ALIVE 😭❤️ I don’t have anywhere I could ever wear this dress, so it’s honestly just getting packed up and going up to the attic for storage for now 😅😅

but now that it’s all done, i am SO ready to start the next project - I think i’m going to do a couple smaller, 1 day projects to get back into the groove of creating before I jump into another big project? After finishing such a BIG, expensive project like this fiber optics dress, I kinda want to just make something fast, cheap, and fun - and not worrying about it being perfect :)
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
The fiber optics dress is DONE!!!! 🎉🎉😭❤️ it’s been 8 months since I bought the fabric, and more hours than I can count making it - but in the end I’m just really, really proud of how it came out :) 

the dress itself is actually super easy to move in! you have to be careful not to damage the fabric, and I had 4 battery packs stuffed under my clothes - but aside from that it honestly just feels like you are wearing a normal dress. and of course, no matter where you go you can always see where you are going - it is really really bright like a flashlight 🤣🤣

I’ve still got a few more videos to edit for this dress (part 2 progress video and a full YouTube tutorial coming soon!) but now we get to do the fun part - start looking for new project ideas!! I’ve got a couple ideas on what to make next but nothing solid - so feel free to leave suggestions the comments below! :D

and a big thank you so much to everyone who came along the journey with me to make this dress - it was a long haul, but we did it!! ❤️

dress inspired by the 2016 met gala dress by @zacposen 
photos taken by my mom :)
.
.

the sleeves for the fiber optics dress are done!! and that means that the entire fiber optics dress is finally… done??!!? (swipe to see whole dress together!)

I’ve still got to add the lining to hide all the wires, (so ignore all those sticking out right now haha) but aside from that this really is the end - we made it!!!! it feels like I’ve been working on this dress FOREVER, but I really am so so happy with how it came out :) 

I’m planning on doing the final photoshoot of the whole dress this weekend, and then I can finally post the part 2 video for this dress soon after! and then it’s off to the next project!! :D 
.
.

fiber optics dress progress - the top is coming along nicely!! not gonna lie, i was really hesitant to how the deep V was going to work out in the beginning but i am absolutely loving the way it’s coming together :)

the bodice still has a lot left to do, but it’s starting to come together and is at least semi-wearable now! I honestly can’t wait until it’s wearable enough to try it on with the skirt - I think I’m going to be able to finish the whole dress this month!! fingers crossed!! 

as always, tons more info about how the bodice was made in my story highlights, so check those out if you want more information! also a huge shout out to everyone who votes in my stories, I absolutely love hearing your feedback and it’s so helpful to get other people’s opinions :D

(a bit of description on the pictures - on the left is the under structure of the bodice with the boning, and on the right is both the fiber optics fabric and the understructure put together and lit up!)

.
.
.
.

making a fiber optics dress, part 1: the skirt! part 2 will be the top (and I’ll post a story in a bit to vote on what the design for the top should be!) 

but after months - this skirt is finally DONE!!! it’s 4 layers (hoopskirt, petticoat, lining, fiber optics fabric) and if i were getting married anytime soon you can BET i would be planning on making this my wedding dress, i love it so much 😤💕💕 

to be totally honest though, this isn’t a super difficult dress - it’s a little complicated because of the fabric, but not too hard. the real reason it took me months is because it’s such an expensive fabric that I had a big mental block trying to get it ~perfect~ (because i quite literally cannot afford to mess up haha 😅😅). but honestly? sometimes done is better than perfect, and that’s the route I’m trying to take with this right now, not getting so hung up on the details! :) but now I’m finally making solid progress on this dress, and I hope to finish it completely in the coming weeks!

and as always - more details are in my story highlights! But with all that said, it’s time to start working on the top!
.
.
.
.
.

🍄🍄 making a mushroom dress!🍄🍄 

this dress was actually made BEFORE the black widow dress, but with the rush to make the black widow dress and life happening, I forgot to post it here! so here is how i made my mushroom dress (in 4 days oof this was another quick project!) 🍄

I have a bunch more info on how i made it on my stories, but i also made a FULL, STEP BY STEP YOUTUBE TUTORIAL!! 🎉🎉🎉 that right yall, a full tutorial, not just a 30 second montage haha - i’m trying to get back into the habit of making YouTube videos, so hopefully this helps anyone that wants to make their own mushroom dress! 

but sorry for the silence this past week! after making so many dresses in such a short time, my body forced me to catch up on sleep and take a bit of a break. 😅 but now I’m well rested and ready to get back to sewing - starting with finishing up the fiber optics dress!! 😤😤⚡️⚡️
.

.

making a dress for the black widow premiere, the night before the premiere 😅😅 despite the fact that this was a 1 day project though, I’m pretty happy with how it came out!! i love the high slit :D

but this dress was based of of @elithienart’s black widow art! I’ve gotten a few questions about patterns but unfortunately since i draped it I can’t help too much on that front - the skirt is just a 1/3 circle skirt though! 

a huge thank you @disneyplus for inviting me to this black widow premiere!!! this was one of the coolest things ive gotten to experience and the movie was incredible - I’m already planning to see it once it comes to theaters july 9th!
